## Vulnerability 5 — `removeLeadingAndTrailingSlashesFrom` Strips Only One Slash (Low)
**File:** `src/main/java/spark/utils/StringUtils.java:393-406`
```java
public static String removeLeadingAndTrailingSlashesFrom(String string) {
String trimmed = string;
if (trimmed.endsWith("/") || trimmed.endsWith("\\")) {
trimmed = trimmed.substring(0, trimmed.length() - 1);  // removes only ONE
}
if (trimmed.startsWith("/")) {
trimmed = trimmed.substring(1);  // removes only ONE
}
return trimmed;
}
```
If a path contains multiple leading slashes (e.g., `//var/www/static/file.txt`), only one slash is stripped. This results in `isPathWithinFolder` receiving `"/var/www/static/file.txt"` (with one remaining leading slash) vs. `"var/www/static"` for the folder — the `startsWith` check fails, causing a false negative that might either **block legitimate requests** or be leveraged to **confuse downstream path handling** depending on how the double-slash was introduced."
